import java.util.*;

class Ribbons {
    public int maxLength(int[] ribbons, int k, int max) {
        int l = 1, r = max;
        while(l < r) {
            int mid = l + (r - l + 1) / 2;
            if(!possible(ribbons, k , mid))
                r = mid - 1;
            else
                l = mid;
        }
        
        return possible(ribbons, k , l) ? l : 0;
    }
    
    private boolean possible(int[] ribbons, int k, int n) {
        int count = 0;
        for(int r : ribbons)
            count += (r / n);
        return count >= k;
    }

	{
		Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
		int N=sc.nextInt();
		int K=sc.nextInt();
		int max=0;
		int mat[]=new int[N];
		for(int j=0;j<N;j++){
			mat[j]=sc.nextInt();
			if(max<mat[j])
				max=mat[j];
		}
		System.out.println(new Ribbons().maxLength(mat,K,max));
	}
